description: The dictators of today aren't united by ideology, writes Anne Applebaum: They operate like companies, focused on preserving their wealth, repressing their people and maintaining power at all costs.
title: These dictators are different. 'Autocracy, Inc.' explains how

description: Chu takes his inspiration from his dad, a Chinese immigrant who worked both the front room and the kitchen of their family-run restaurant: "The guy that in the back of the kitchen, that was my hero."
title: 'Wicked' director Jon M. Chu says creativity isn't magic — it's hard work

description: Dinaw Mengestu's ingenuity and eloquence as a writer are on display in this novel about an Ethiopian American man who returns home only to learn that his father has just died.
title: 'Someone Like Us' is a fresh, idiosyncratic novel about immigrating to the U.S.

description: The verdict is in, and the ending is a dud: Rather than wriggling out of the original story’s sexism, the Apple TV+ series just makes the same mistakes in a new way.
title: 'Presumed Innocent' finale: And the murderer is ...

description: Every album the rapper has released since 2000 has hit No. 1 on the Billboard 200. The Death of Slim Shady (Coup de Grace) extends his streak. Also: Shaboozey returns to the top of the singles chart.
title: Eminem breaks Taylor Swift’s 12-week run atop the album chart

description: The Israeli leader speaks Wednesday to a joint meeting of Congress amid the ongoing Israel-Hamas war in Gaza. Republicans are strongly supportive of Israel, while Democrats are increasingly critical.
title: Israel's Benjamin Netanyahu can expect a mixed reception as he addresses Congress
